1
00:00:10,333 --> 00:00:12,000
<i> I already told him.</i>

2
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:13,267
<i> I don't know,</i>

3
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,900
<i>that demon's whispering
to him is even more intense.</i>

4
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:15,833
<i> Which demon?</i>

5
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:16,667
<i> His boss.</i>

6
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,867
<i> Rictus Grin.</i>

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,933
<i>That's what the scary smile
left on Sonny's face</i>

8
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:22,367
<i> is called when he died.</i>

9
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:23,900
<i> I told him!</i>

10
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:27,533
<i> Strychnine poisoning,</i>

11
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:29,733
<i>test positive someone poisoned
Sonny.</i>

12
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:32,467
<i>Maybe this is something worth
looking into.</i>

13
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,033
<i> Will you investigate Amo?</i>

14
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:39,000
<i>I, Victor Santiago, will be
affected by a blind item?</i>

15
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:40,633
<i> Mira, before I forget,</i>

16
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,267
<i>you're the one I'm assigning
to the league.</i>

17
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:43,600
<i>- Go ahead.
- Just do your job.</i>

18
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:46,767
<i>I'll just remind you,
if you keep playing dirty,</i>

19
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,233
<i> it will all bite back.</i>

20
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:49,600
<i>Do you have any idea where
this is coming from?</i>

21
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:50,900
<i> No, Sir.</i>

22
00:00:51,033 --> 00:00:52,233
<i>Don't continue with your
investigation of Amo for now.</i>

23
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:53,600
<i> What do you mean?</i>

24
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:55,533
<i>Is your father involved in this?</i>

25
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:58,500
<i>If he is, he wouldn't like what
I'm going to do.</i>

26
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:01,800
<i> Can I talk to you, Son?</i>

27
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:13,800
What is this about?

28
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:19,633
I'm sure you've seen the blind
item that says I'm involved

29
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,500
in the San Isidro bank robbery.

30
00:01:24,233 --> 00:01:30,033
If you came here to ask
if the info came from us,

31
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:32,400
you're mistaken.

32
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,567
Wait a minute, Tonyo.

33
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:41,967
That's not what I came here for.

34
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:45,300
I don't care what people
think of me.

35
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:48,233
I'm only thinking about you,
Son.

36
00:01:48,367 --> 00:01:50,867
I want you to know firsthand

37
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,667
that I had nothing to do
with that.

38
00:01:54,833 --> 00:02:00,367
I was not a good father to you,
but I'm not a criminal, Tonyo,

39
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:06,100
and I won't do anything
to harm Lara.

40
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:06,967
Please,

41
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:11,600
don't you dare mention her name
here.

42
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,367
Sorry,

43
00:02:15,533 --> 00:02:16,233
but...

44
00:02:18,033 --> 00:02:21,333
I don't want you to be affected
by this blind item

45
00:02:21,467 --> 00:02:22,400
that's spreading.

46
00:02:22,533 --> 00:02:23,700
I'm a cop.

47
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:28,167
I don't believe in blind items.

48
00:02:28,300 --> 00:02:29,367
Is that all?

49
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,500
You can leave now.

50
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:33,200
Thank you for listening.

51
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,533
I hope everything you say
is true.

52
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:43,433
Because if I prove

53
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:47,267
that you have something to do
with what happened to my wife,

54
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:52,400
you won't like what I can do.

55
00:03:50,767 --> 00:03:51,400
Tonyo.

56
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:57,900
What are you doing here?

57
00:03:58,033 --> 00:04:00,400
I saw you buy some alcohol.

58
00:04:00,533 --> 00:04:01,867
Maybe you want someone
to drink with?

59
00:04:03,133 --> 00:04:05,700
Why would I have a drink with
you?

60
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:07,900
I just want to be with you, son.

61
00:04:09,467 --> 00:04:15,533
Me, I don't want to,
so just leave me alone.

62
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:18,433
Go away.

63
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:46,233
When we find this strychnine,

64
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:49,700
we'll definitely be able to find
a lead on who killed Sonny.

65
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:52,867
Wait, wait, wait.

66
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:56,267
Is this the new Antonio Conde?

67
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,867
Taking notes?

68
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,200
More organized?

69
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,900
What are you talking about,
Garcia?

70
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:06,733
No, I just noticed.
You weren't like that before.

71
00:05:06,867 --> 00:05:10,533
I feel like you're adapting
to my style.

72
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:11,967
You're getting it, aren't you?

73
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:14,767
Okay, it came from you.

74
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:16,367
He finally admitted it.

75
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,900
He got it from me.

76
00:05:18,033 --> 00:05:22,833
But wait, Conde, why is the term
old on your list?

77
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,533
Because this has been banned
for a long time

78
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:29,433
due to its toxic properties.

79
00:05:29,567 --> 00:05:32,167
Yes, by the way.
I met a botanist.

80
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:35,200
He has toxic and exotic plants.

81
00:05:35,367 --> 00:05:37,200
That's where Dizon
and I are going later.

82
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:41,767
So you, Garcia, Robles,
find someone to talk to

83
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:44,533
about inside info in the black
market about toxic chemicals.

84
00:05:44,667 --> 00:05:45,500
Wait, wait.

85
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:48,833
Conde, maybe it would be better

86
00:05:48,967 --> 00:05:50,767
if the two of us
who will go there,

87
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:54,467
and then Dizon and Robles
would be left here.

88
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:58,367
Why?

89
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:01,133
Do you think we won't be
transparent when we get leads?

90
00:06:02,267 --> 00:06:03,900
No, it's not like that.

91
00:06:04,033 --> 00:06:07,233
Ah, to be more balanced.

92
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,567
Wait, wait.

93
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,567
What do you mean
by more balanced?

94
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:16,533
More balanced, I mean,
when you look at a case,

95
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:20,200
it's better to have old eyes,
and have fresh eyes.

96
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:23,200
Different perspective, right?

97
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:24,400
Gets?

98
00:06:24,533 --> 00:06:28,633
There, it's like old and
then young, something like that.

99
00:06:28,767 --> 00:06:30,367
Old, young.

100
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,467
I mean, a different perspective.

101
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,400
Oh, okay.

102
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:35,833
Let's go, let's not waste time.

103
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:38,200
Let's go.

104
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:46,167
Robles!

105
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:47,433
Let's go!

106
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:53,633
Hey, porridge.

107
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,033
Porridge?

108
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,233
Who's sick?

109
00:06:57,733 --> 00:06:58,267
I think it's Kapitana.

110
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,133
Oh, maybe she has a fever.

111
00:06:59,267 --> 00:06:59,767
Joke.

112
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:00,700
Hey, I'll go first, huh?

113
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:01,733
Your face is really thick,
isn't it?

114
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:02,800
- That's right.
- Me too, can I have some?

115
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:04,000
I'll give it to you, oh.

116
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:04,900
Hello!

117
00:07:05,033 --> 00:07:06,767
Hello, Kapitana!

118
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:07,800
Are you eating?

119
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:10,333
Yes, Kapitana!

120
00:07:10,467 --> 00:07:12,133
I wish you were our grandmother,
right?

121
00:07:12,267 --> 00:07:14,567
That's right.
Actually, Kapitana, do you know?

122
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:17,100
This is probably the most
delicious porridge

123
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:19,233
I've ever tasted in my entire
life.

124
00:07:20,533 --> 00:07:22,133
- Correct.
- Amazing! Perfect!

125
00:07:22,267 --> 00:07:23,467
You know, Kapitana,

126
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,300
I'm excited with what you'll
cook for dinner later!

127
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,800
What will Kapitana cook
for dinner?

128
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:31,367
Kapitana,
we don't eat fried food

129
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:33,667
