banning you.

144
00:07:58,433 --> 00:08:00,233
No choice, Grandmother.

145
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:01,467
I have to obey Chief.

146
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,233
The more I can't get close
to Amo.

147
00:08:05,367 --> 00:08:08,633
Isn't Amo going to be a guest
later in the basketball game?

148
00:08:08,767 --> 00:08:09,533
Yes, right?

149
00:08:09,667 --> 00:08:10,633
That's too bad, Bobby.

150
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:13,467
You know, if you just agreed
to be the muse,

151
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,967
then you can get close to Amo.

152
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,500
- Yes.
- Right?

153
00:08:17,633 --> 00:08:18,433
We should be the muse, right?

154
00:08:18,567 --> 00:08:19,567
What if we'll be the muse?

155
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:20,700
No, just me.

156
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:27,100
Good morning everyone
and welcome

157
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:35,100
to the Inter-barangay Basketball
League 2025 Finals!

158
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:38,400
To start our competition today,

159
00:08:38,533 --> 00:08:40,733
let's call out our opposing
team,

160
00:08:40,867 --> 00:08:46,600
let's applaud Barangay
San Martin!

161
00:08:58,333 --> 00:09:00,400
Hey Dude, let's go one
on one sometime.

162
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:01,533
You're such a flirt!

163
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:09,333
And of course,
our home team is here!

164
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:12,767
Let's give it up
to Barangay Sta. Fe!

165
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,033
Oh, Bobby!

166
00:09:18,133 --> 00:09:20,667
My granddaughter is beautiful!
Beautiful!

167
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,500
Isn't she, Grandmother?

168
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:24,667
We fixed her up.

169
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,767
Beautiful?

170
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:26,400
Perfect, isn't she?

171
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:27,900
Yes. I did her hair.

172
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:29,067
Even if you don't fix her,

173
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,000
she's beautiful because she
inherited her beauty

174
00:09:30,133 --> 00:09:31,500
from her Grandmother.

175
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:32,667
My granddaughter!

176
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:35,100
- She inherited it from me.
- She's beautiful, oh.

177
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:36,300
Bobby!

178
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:38,400
And this time,
ladies and gentlemen,

179
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:46,333
let's welcome
Mr. Victor "Amo" Santiago!

180
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:47,333
Wow! Awesome!

181
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:52,067
Good morning to all of us.

182
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:55,533
Let's listen to the supporters
of this,

183
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:58,567
Barangay San Martin team!

184
00:09:58,700 --> 00:09:59,733
Applause!

185
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:09,133
Will Barangay Sta. Fe
be defeated?

186
00:10:09,267 --> 00:10:11,533
Where are the supporters,
let's applaud!

187
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:16,467
Sta. Fe! Sta. Fe!

188
00:10:17,567 --> 00:10:21,533
I have a feeling that
today's battle

189
00:10:21,667 --> 00:10:24,200
of the teams will be, exciting.

190
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:30,000
The promoters and I have
discussed that the prize money

191
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:34,200
for the champion would be
100,000 pesos!

192
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,000
That's awesome!

193
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:43,500
But that's not true
because I made it 250,000 pesos!

194
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:44,433
Is that okay?

195
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:48,633
Is that okay?

196
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,233
That's right,

197
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:56,200
that's why I am grateful to all
of you for inviting me here.

198
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:58,300
Let's not delay this any longer.

199
00:10:58,433 --> 00:11:01,167
Let's start the battle!

200
00:11:26,967 --> 00:11:27,600
Bro!

201
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,267
Dude!

202
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:31,700
It seems like there will be
trouble here.

203
00:11:47,267 --> 00:11:48,767
Boss Tonyo needs to know this,
Brad.

204
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,100
- Come on.
- Let's go.

205
00:11:57,133 --> 00:12:01,867
Defense! There you go, defense.
Hey, man, here we go.

206
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,500
- Shoot! Shoot!
- Amazing!

207
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,700
Perfect!

208
00:12:09,367 --> 00:12:12,000
Hey! Defense!

209
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:26,933
Shoot! Shoot!
Amazing! Perfect!

210
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,333
Defense!

211
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:35,033
Defense!

212
00:12:35,167 --> 00:12:36,467
Defense!

213
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:41,667
It's okay not to shoot.
He's handsome.

214
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:42,633
That's why.

215
00:12:46,367 --> 00:12:47,800
Bobby, I'll goahead first, okay?

216
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,400
I need to go to the municipal
office.

217
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:51,967
- I'll leave you here, okay?
- Okay, Grandmother.

218
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:53,000
Be careful, okay?

219
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:54,300
- Oh, okay.
- Kapitana.

220
00:12:54,433 --> 00:12:55,700
We'll stay behind.

221
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:56,833
Ah, are you going to be left
behind?

222
00:12:56,967 --> 00:12:58,933
Yes, because there are so many
handsome men here.

223
00:12:59,067 --> 00:13:00,167
Okay, are you going to be left
behind?

224
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:01,767
You don't have a job anymore.

225
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:02,667
You don't have a job anymore.

226
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,500
- Bye.
- Bobby, we'll take care of it.

227
00:13:04,633 --> 00:13:05,067
Grandmother.

228
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,300
Okay, okay.

229
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:08,533
Kapitana, can't you take a joke?
That's right.

230
00:13:10,367 --> 00:13:11,800
It's really like that.

231
00:13:11,933 --> 00:13:13,700
It's fun, fun.

232
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:18,133
Good day, Amo.

233
00:13:18,267 --> 00:13:19,967
A good day too.

234
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,333
Sergeant Enriquez?

235
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,333
I knew it, it's you!

236
00:13:25,367 --> 00:13:28,367
The muse from the other side

237
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:29,833
doesn't stand a chance against
you.

238
00:13:29,967 --> 00:13:32,533
No way.

239
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:36,567
Good to see you here, ah.

240
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:41,333
I thought you were here because
you wanted to investigate me.

241
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,033
Investigate?

242
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,333
Why?

243
00:13:47,467 --> 00:13:51,800
Apparently,
based on a blind item,

244
00:13:51,933 --> 00:13:55,500
I'm involved in three cases.

245
00:14:00,733 --> 00:14:05,000
Amo, you probably remember what
we talked about last time,

246
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:09,933
the missing masks were used
in the San Isidro bank robbery.

247
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:12,667
I knew it, okay?

248
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,400
There are some things you want
to know.

249
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:15,400
Okay, okay.

250
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:16,667
Ask questions while it's still
half-time.

251
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,133
Amo, I just want to know...

252
00:14:19,267 --> 00:14:20,467
What you can say,

253
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:25,400
because even the dialogues
of the kidnappers

254
00:14:25,533 --> 00:14:27,700
are the same as in your movies?

255
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:31,800
Actually, even the poison
used on the kidnapper,

256
00:14:31,967 --> 00:14:34,600
the one who kidnapped the
Mayor's daughter,

257
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:38,600
is the same in your movie...

258
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:40,100
The other movie.

259
00:14:41,767 --> 00:14:42,733
Amo, I'm sorry.

260
00:14:42,867 --> 00:14:46,933
I'm not accusing, but of course,

261
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:49,800
I want to know just to be clear

262
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:52,733
about what your reaction
would be,

263
00:14:52,867 --> 00:14:53,833
and what your opinion would be.

264
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:55,033
Maybe, it's like this.

265
00:14:56,933 --> 00:15:00,967
If those criminals
aren't my super fans,

266
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:04,000
then maybe it's just
a coincidence.

267
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:08,100
The only thing that hurts
about coincidence

268
00:15:08,233 --> 00:15:14,433
is that it can be given any
meaning, right?

269
00:15:14,567 --> 00:15:16,933
It depends on what you
want to show.

270
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:20,067
But the second half is about
to start.

271
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:20,867
What?

272
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,767
Enjoy the rest of the game.

273
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,000
Okay.

274
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,233
Is it about to start?

275
00:15:30,633 --> 00:15:32,133
Excuse me, Sir?

276
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:34,367
Ah, we have some toxic plants
here,

277
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:38,633
but we haven't been housing
strychnine for a long time.

278
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,833
Do you know where to get it?

279
00:15:40,967 --> 00:15:42,167
Even if it's illegal.

280
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:45,233
Oh my, Sir, you know, when
it comes to that kind of thing,

281
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:46,700
I don't know anything, Sir.

282
00:15:50,767 --> 00:15:52,200
Okay, thank you.

283
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:53,233
Nothing, Sir.

284
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:56,100
Just anytime you need help,
I'm here, Sir.

285
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:57,333
Okay.

286
00:15:57,467 --> 00:15:58,900
Bok, let's go.

287
00:15:59,033 --> 00:16:00,633
We can't get anything here.

288
00:16:00,767 --> 00:16:02,400
What's the news about Robles?

289
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:10,333
Well, they're still looking
for something legit

290
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:13,167
to buy on the black market,
but there's really nothing.

291
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:17,233
Bok, this case is really
difficult.

292
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:21,000
The person behind this knows
how to cover his tracks.

293
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:23,933
You know, because of that,
I'm getting hungry.

294
00:16:24,067 --> 00:16:25,533
We need protein.

295
00:16:25,667 --> 00:16:26,533
There's an eatery over there.

296
00:16:26,667 --> 00:16:28,767
Come on, let's eat, your treat.

297
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:31,467
- Okay.
- Okay.

298
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,300
I told you, to text him first.

299
00:16:37,433 --> 00:16:38,567
We failed to catch him.

300
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:39,467
Look, it's so far away.

301
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,167
What a waste of time.

302
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,067
I'm neglecting my studies.

303
00:16:43,233 --> 00:16:44,967
Look at my slippers,
they're so dirty.

304
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:48,267
You're so hard-headed,
I don't have any load!

305
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,067
Oh, where are we going
to find Boss Tonyo here?

306
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,433
Look. Where are we going
to find him?

307
00:16:51,567 --> 00:16:55,867
If I see Boss Tonyo,
I'll grind my teeth at him, man.

308
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:56,933
There he is, calling.

309
00:16:57,067 --> 00:16:58,200
Okay, answer it!

310
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:00,000
- Answer it!
- That's it.

311
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:04,133
- Bossing! Bossing!
- I miss you, Boss!

312
00:17:04,267 --> 00:17:05,467
- I miss you!
- Fake.

313
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,867
Hello, Vince.

314
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:07,933
Boss.

315
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:09,933
How are you doing there?
I just have a question.

316
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:15,400
Maybe you have contact with
someone where we can get poison?

317
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:16,600
Depends on the poison, Boss.

318
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:18,033
But let's talk about
that later.

319
00:17:18,167 --> 00:17:21,333
There's going to be trouble
later here in Barangay Sta. Fe.

320
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:23,667
What trouble?

321
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,733
Boss, they say there's going
to be a gang war

322
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:27,167
in the basketball game.

323
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:29,733
Okay, okay, we're going there
now.

324
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:32,333
- What's up, man? Hey.
- Hey, what's up? What's up?

325
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:33,433
Still nothing.
He dropped the call.

326
00:17:33,567 --> 00:17:35,033
You didn't ask for money
for food?

327
00:17:35,167 --> 00:17:35,867
You're so stupid Later!

328
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,733
Calm down! Later!

329
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:42,867
Go! Go! Go!

330
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:44,867
Yes!

331
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:51,900
Nice one!

332
00:18:12,367 --> 00:18:15,667
Timeout, Barangay San Martin!

333
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:20,167
Amo!

334
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:22,433
Good day.

335
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:24,100
Amo, can I have an interview
with you?

336
00:18:24,233 --> 00:18:25,600
Even if it's just
for a short time.

337
00:18:25,733 --> 00:18:29,533
Miss Beautiful, your name
is ringing so loud now.

338
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:33,733
Oh my, Sir, I was just at the
right place at the right time.

339
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:37,033
Is that how you describe
your exclusive interview

340
00:18:37,167 --> 00:18:39,200
with my friend,
Joaquin Guerrero?

341
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:43,800
Look. I don't want to be rude,

342
00:18:43,933 --> 00:18:46,900
but I'm trying to watch
a game here.

343
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:53,033
If you want to know me better,
just observe me and,

344
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:55,167
what you see is what you get?

345
00:18:57,633 --> 00:18:58,833
Enjoy the game.

346
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:00,367
Do you like basketball?

347
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:01,600
Yes.

348
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:02,967
Thank you, Sir.

349
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,867
What's that?

350
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,467
Not counted!

351
00:19:33,033 --> 00:19:37,500
My beloved countrymen,
the ending is something else!

352
00:19:37,633 --> 00:19:38,900
What a great match!

353
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:43,167
Well, of course, first,

354
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:47,833
I want to congratulate the
organizers of our League,

355
00:19:47,967 --> 00:19:49,000
of course, right?

356
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:51,033
And you know,
you're all great...

357
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:52,400
You are all great.

358
00:19:52,533 --> 00:19:56,400
But, of course,
there's only one winner.

359
00:19:56,533 --> 00:19:58,100
Congratulations,

360
00:19:58,233 --> 00:20:01,267
Barangay San Martin,
for being the champion!

361
00:20:02,433 --> 00:20:12,400
And, you will win a trophy
and the amount of 250,000!

362
00:20:12,633 --> 00:20:14,600
All right, all right.

363
00:20:14,733 --> 00:20:15,600
That's it, okay.

364
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,267
My countrymen, 'til next year.

365
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:25,233
I hope this happens again next
year!

366
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:29,633
Well, I'll try to make
that 250,000 even bigger.

367
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:31,467
All right, thank you, thank you!

368
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:35,733
By the way, I wanted
to stay here longer,

369
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:38,600
but we have another place to go.

370
00:20:38,733 --> 00:20:41,533
These guys have been asking me
to go for a while now,

371
00:20:41,667 --> 00:20:42,533
all right, all right.

372
00:20:42,667 --> 00:20:43,567
I'll go ahead of you.

373
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,567
Thank you very much, okay.

374
00:20:49,667 --> 00:20:51,700
San Martin!

375
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:53,433
San Martin!

376
00:20:53,567 --> 00:20:55,333
Hey, man.

377
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:56,700
That's great.

378
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:58,333
You have our trophy.

379
00:20:58,467 --> 00:20:59,567
Give it to me.

380
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:03,300
Hey, give it back, wait.

381
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:05,567
Don't tell us this is your
territory,

382
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,267
we won't turn you away.

383
00:21:09,733 --> 00:21:12,767
Well, if you want it, get it.

384
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:13,767
You're so arrogant.

385
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:14,600
Hit him!

386
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,100
Garcia, call for a backup!

387
00:21:36,933 --> 00:21:38,033
Oh, what?

388
00:21:39,367 --> 00:21:41,867
Help!

389
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:44,467
You're stupid,
I'm not related to him.

390
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:55,300
- Ma'am, are you okay? The Kid?
- You better be ready.

391
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,833
Mother, get out, quick!

392
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:13,567
Come on, quick!

393
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,100
Enriquez, are you okay?

394
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:16,400
I'm okay, Sir!

395
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:25,233
That's four.

396
00:22:25,367 --> 00:22:27,600
I'll have three and one for you.

397
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:29,300
Sir, you're unfair.

398
00:22:29,433 --> 00:22:30,800
Let's have two each.

399
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:44,300
Sir!

400
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:53,800
Sir, those three are mine?

401
00:22:55,467 --> 00:22:56,400
What?

402
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:57,167
All right!

403
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:07,833
I have the money! Let's go!

404
00:23:09,467 --> 00:23:11,233
Enriquez, let's go!

405
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:14,467
Hold this, hold this!

406
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:17,633
Hey, hey, come here. Stay here!

407
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:18,567
Don't come any closer!

408
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:19,300
I'll kill him!

409
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:21,600
I'll kill him!

410
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:24,100
Stay there!

411
00:23:24,233 --> 00:23:25,867
Come in, come in!

412
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:26,967
Don't come any closer!

413
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,867
Amo, let's get out of here.

414
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,300
Why? What's going on?

415
00:23:33,433 --> 00:23:35,500
They say a gang leader hostage
someone.

416
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:38,800
Stay here.

417
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:43,400
What's your plan, Daga?

418
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,133
Everyone, get out of there!

419
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:49,567
Get us a car so we can escape

420
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:52,367
or else we'll kill him!

421
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:54,867
What?

422
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,467
Wait, wait!

423
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,367
What's going on here?

424
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:15,633
Someone's being hostage.

425
00:24:15,767 --> 00:24:18,067
Maybe I can help.
Let me try to talk to them.

426
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:19,900
Amo is impressive, isn't he?

427
00:24:20,033 --> 00:24:21,767
He interfered in the police
operation.

428
00:24:21,900 --> 00:24:24,633
If he gets killed or a hostage
gets hurt,

429
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:25,900
